<span id="freeTextContainer9759580104680835738">UHG! no no no! This book is bad news. John teaches a man to live according to the wild nature of his flesh, rather than according to the grace and love of the Spirit of God. As if a man can be spiritually free if He&apos;s emotionally free and wild? This is not the message of Christ, nor His gospel.<br/><br/>Christ didn&apos;t come with an attitude of macho-ism. He came in meekness gentleness and love. He is an all powerful God, and He is not a containable God, but that doesn&apos;t make Him wild like the nature of the </span>
  <span id="freeText9759580104680835738" style="display:none">UHG! no no no! This book is bad news. John teaches a man to live according to the wild nature of his flesh, rather than according to the grace and love of the Spirit of God. As if a man can be spiritually free if He's emotionally free and wild? This is not the message of Christ, nor His gospel.<br /><br />Christ didn't come with an attitude of macho-ism. He came in meekness gentleness and love. He is an all powerful God, and He is not a containable God, but that doesn't make Him wild like the nature of the flesh! This book is down right blasphemous!<br /><br />I'm kicking myself at this point for not burning the book while I had the chance. Instead I just threw it out.<br /><br />Do yourself a favor, and do the same.</span>
